UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426699000722
KW  - Index futures
KW  - Overreaction
KW  - Market efficiency
AB  - We observe intraday price reversals following large price changes at the opening of the S&P 500 Futures market and the HSI Futures market. We note that the magnitude of subsequent price reversals is positively related to the initial price changes, and that the price reversals are not caused by a bid–ask spread, or by panic among investors. We also note that such price reversals can be exploited to give rise to profitable opportunities after transaction costs, even though these may not be very significant. This study shows that investor overreaction may be a universal phenomenon and irrational investor behavior like overreaction may also exist among groups of sophisticated investors.
ER  - 

